  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sexual Diversity and Spirituality</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Technical advice to CAid partner organizations to incorporate a work perspective that promotes and respects sexual diversity. Pedagogical advice to CAid partners for the drafting of didactic materials that facilitate the incorporation of the sexual and gender diversity approach in their work plans. Identify local experiences of rapprochement that have occurred between LGBT people and progressive religious sectors. Encourage dialogues between LGBT leaders with religious sectors that support diversity. Promote exchanges of experiences between religious sectors that have incorporated sexual diversity into their processes. Dissemination of positive experiences of rapprochement between religious sectors and LGBT people.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimes at social organizations having the tools to incorporate sexual diversity into their workto contribute to promoting a culture of peace, respect for diversity and non-discrimination against LGBT people. Also, to build bridges between religious sectors and LGBT people to contribute to the elimination of imaginaries that produce or sustain discrimination, reduces barriers and mutual distrust through agreements and improves coexistence.</narrative>
  </description>
